Prime Minister Kassim Majaliwa has today, Saturday, launched a new Tanzania Broadcasting Cooperation (TBC)'s Tanzania Safari Channel designated to promote the country's tourism industry. The Premier said the channel will be a great catalyst in promoting tourist attractions available in the country hence increase number of both local and foreign tourists visiting them. PM ordered the Ministry of Works, Transport and Communication to continue gardening-up the road from the Julius Nyerere International Airport (JNIA) to Kamata as well as installing lights that will lighten up the area at night. “That area should be attractive especially to foreign visitors that arrive at night, there should also be billboards along the road that advertise our attractions,” he added. Majaliwa noted that currently the country receives 1.3 milioni tourists annually and the government goal is to host up to two million tourists annually coming 2020.